user_query:
Help me make a hard decision: my bootstrapped SaaS has a $4.2M acquisition offer versus raising a seed and continuing independently. Please read input/context.txt for details about our business metrics, team, runway, personal considerations, risks, and the assumptions I'm making. Using that context, do not give me direct advice yet. Instead, ask me back the right questions and structure the decision so I can think clearly.

Deliverables (write all files under output/):
1) Write output/questions.json with this schema and minimum counts:
   {
     "surface_question": string,
     "real_question": string,
     "taxonomy": {
       "clarifying": [>=3 strings],
       "reframing": [>=3 strings],
       "assumption_surfacing": [>=2 strings],
       "decision_forcing": [>=2 strings],
       "root_cause": {
         "problem_statement": string,
         "five_whys": [
           {"why": 1, "answer": string},
           {"why": 2, "answer": string},
           {"why": 3, "answer": string},
           {"why": 4, "answer": string},
           {"why": 5, "answer": string}
         ]
       }
     },
     "answerability": {
       "answerable_now": [>=1 string],
       "answerable_later": [>=1 string],
       "unanswerable": [>=1 string]
     }
   }
   Make the questions specific to the details in input/context.txt (not generic) and ensure surface_question and real_question are distinct.

2) Write output/decision_framework.md with clearly labeled sections for Step 1 through Step 6 (define, options, criteria, evaluate, test, decide). In Step 2 list at least 3 real options as bullet points. In Step 3 list at least 4 decision criteria before any evaluation. In Step 4 include a simple pipe-delimited evaluation table with a header row and at least 4 columns (criteria) and at least 3 option rows. In Step 5 include a regret and gut-check test. In Step 6 note the decision reversibility and a provisional decision threshold.

3) Write output/action_plan.txt listing exactly the top 5 next actions to reduce uncertainty, one per line, each line tagged with one of: [answerable now], [answerable later], or [unanswerable]. Ground each action in the specifics from input/context.txt.

All outputs should be derived from the context file and reflect my constraints and assumptions. Focus on asking high-quality questions and structuring my thinking rather than giving prescriptive advice.
